annotationA: RT07324p; ATP binding; microtubule binding; microtubule motor activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: microtubule-based movement; Belongs to the TRAFAC class myosin-kinesin ATPase superfamily. Kinesin family
annotationB: Transforming acidic coiled-coil protein (Tacc) is a centrosomal protein that helps to stabilize microtubules. It seems to influence microtubules indirectly, primarily through its interaction with msps. Tacc is also phosphorylated by aurA, and this activates its ability to stabilize microtubules
